---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Deer Camp"
  description="Deer Camp: more than a place. Why May matters, the road in, and the November tradition that brings everyone home."
>
  <section class="pt-32 pb-20 px-6 max-w-5xl mx-auto bg-cream-2">
    <p class="eyebrow block mb-3">The Place</p>
    <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl mb-4">Deer Camp: More Than a Place</h1>
    <p class="opacity-80 max-w-2xl mb-10">
      It starts in May, long before the first frost — clearing the road, opening the cabin,
      getting ready for a November that's still six months away.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 items-start">
      <div class="space-y-4 opacity-85">
        <p>
          Why May matters: the road in has to be cleared, the cabin opened and aired out, and the
          camp readied long before anyone thinks about a rifle. It's the part nobody films, but
          it's the part that makes November possible.
        </p>
        <p>
          Then November arrives — the hunt, but also the meals cooked too big for the table, the
          fires that run too late, the stories told one too many times and somehow funnier each time.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-cream border-l-4 border-gold px-6 py-5">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-lg mb-1">Camp prep, every spring</h3>
          <p class="text-sm opacity-80">Clearing the road in, opening the cabin, the first fire of the season.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-cream border-l-4 border-gold px-6 py-5">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-lg mb-1">Camp life, every fall</h3>
          <p class="text-sm opacity-80">The hunt, the meals, the fires, the laughter that doesn't make it into any film.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-12">
      <a href="/gallery/" class="text-gold underline hover:text-gold-soft">See photos from camp &rarr;</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
